**Abstract:**
A French-language abstract (resume) for an article on "Metaphysics and Eucharist in Leibniz's Early Writings." The document describes how Leibniz's early effort to link Mechanical Philosophy to theism emphasized God as First Mover, while his growing desire to defend the intelligibility of Transubstantiation inspired deeper metaphysical analyses of substantiality and divine union with the world. It explores how Leibniz's Paris stay created tension between his metaphysics and his Transubstantiation defense, relating this to the principle of equipollence.

**AI Recommendation:** Abstract for a Leibniz article; shows author's interest in the relationship between metaphysics and Eucharistic theology.

